
// Executes a workflow action named "openai-query" from a specified file, passing in arguments such as the model name, maximum tokens, and context. It loads instructions from a file and uses the current node's value as the query. The [execute] slot is used to invoke the action, and [io.file.load] is utilized to load the instruction content.
execute:magic.workflows.actions.execute
   name:openai-query
   filename:/modules/openai/workflows/actions/openai-query.hl
   arguments
      model:gpt-4-1106-preview
      max_tokens:int:1500
      context:x:@execute/@execute/*/context
      instruction:x:@io.file.load
      query:x:@.dp/#
